Class C2SInteractive

  • java.lang.Object
    • production.C2SInteractive

  • class C2SInteractive
extends java.lang.Object
    Class for running the translation part of the tool through the terminal. This is opposed to running the tool with a file containing a list of Cypher queries.

      • run_debug

        static void run_debug(java.io.File f_cypher,
                      java.io.File f_sql,
                      java.lang.String dbName)
        Method for running the tool in debug mode, where information about the queries is recorded, and where printing the results to a local file is possible.
        Parameters:
        f_cypher - File object to store the results from Neo4j.
        f_sql - File object to store the results from Postgres.
        dbName - Name of the relational database that the generated SQL will be executed on.

      • run

        static void run(java.lang.String dbName)
        Method for running the tool in its normal operation, where Cypher is inputted into the console, and then the results are outputted to the console, but from the relational database.
        Parameters:
        dbName - Name of the relational database that the translated query is to be executed on.
